WEBVTT

00:05.296 --> 00:06.006
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:08.091 --> 00:09.759
<i>In my vision,
you were surrounded</i>

00:09.759 --> 00:11.219
<i>by these red flowers.</i>

00:11.219 --> 00:13.054
You were dead.

00:13.054 --> 00:14.389
<i>So you did find something.</i>

00:14.389 --> 00:15.849
After everything
we've been through,

00:15.849 --> 00:17.308
you still don't trust me?

00:17.308 --> 00:18.810
<i>Ella's never abandoned me.</i>

00:18.810 --> 00:20.603
<i>There's no way
I'm abandoning her.</i>

00:20.603 --> 00:21.855
I'm not gonna make it.

00:21.855 --> 00:23.273
<i>I love you.</i>

00:23.273 --> 00:24.691
<i>Sometimes it just feels</i>

00:24.691 --> 00:26.067
<i>like other people
are moving on,</i>

00:26.067 --> 00:27.777
making new memories here.

00:27.777 --> 00:29.529
Mine are all still back home.

00:29.529 --> 00:30.864
<i>Whatever progress
you've made</i>

00:30.864 --> 00:32.866
<i>against the cancer
goes away immediately</i>

00:32.866 --> 00:34.701
if you're not doing
consistent treatment.

00:34.701 --> 00:36.327
Get to the infirmary.
There's nobody there.

00:36.327 --> 00:37.537
You can get your pills.

00:37.537 --> 00:39.873
This project has taken
everything from me.

00:39.873 --> 00:41.082
I gotta stop it.

00:41.082 --> 00:42.167
<i>Those explosives will</i>

00:42.167 --> 00:43.668
<i>destroy the entire building.</i>

00:43.668 --> 00:45.337
I made a promise to my family
to get them home.

00:45.337 --> 00:46.838
<i>You need to give this up.</i>

00:46.838 --> 00:48.340
<i>It's not gonna stop.</i>

00:51.259 --> 00:54.054
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

00:54.054 --> 00:56.264
[explosion booms,
glass shatters]

00:56.264 --> 01:01.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:01.478 --> 01:04.439
[grunting]

01:12.197 --> 01:13.198
Levi!

01:13.198 --> 01:14.574
[coughing]

01:16.034 --> 01:16.910
You guys made it.

01:16.910 --> 01:18.912
Yeah.

01:18.912 --> 01:20.622
Here, help me get this off him.

01:20.622 --> 01:22.665
[all grunting]

01:22.665 --> 01:24.584
[explosion booms]

01:26.127 --> 01:27.128
We've got to move.

01:27.128 --> 01:28.963
We're running out of time here.

01:28.963 --> 01:29.923
Save yourselves.

01:29.923 --> 01:31.758
Leave me.

01:31.758 --> 01:32.759
Get out of here.

01:32.759 --> 01:33.802
Dad, we can't.

01:33.802 --> 01:35.470
We have to help him.

01:38.139 --> 01:39.766
Get out of here!

01:39.766 --> 01:40.725
Come on.

01:44.020 --> 01:45.855
Ty, help me.

01:45.855 --> 01:47.315
I'm gonna lift this up.

01:47.315 --> 01:48.733
You pull him out.

01:48.733 --> 01:51.236
[both grunting]

01:51.236 --> 01:53.321
Ah!
[groaning]

02:02.706 --> 02:05.375
[gasping]

02:05.375 --> 02:12.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:15.760 --> 02:18.722
<i>[intense music]</i>

02:18.722 --> 02:20.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:21.975 --> 02:24.978
<i>[Angelo De Augustine's
"All Your Life"]</i>

02:24.978 --> 02:31.317
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:31.317 --> 02:33.194
The building's gone.

02:33.194 --> 02:35.321
I don't know
how we're gonna get home.

02:35.321 --> 02:37.240
We'll figure it out.

02:37.240 --> 02:41.911
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:41.911 --> 02:44.706
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

02:44.706 --> 02:50.295
<i>♪ Thought I'd go and leave ♪</i>

02:50.295 --> 02:53.965
<i>♪ Anyway time recalls ♪</i>

02:53.965 --> 02:59.054
<i>♪ All your life,
all your life, all your life ♪</i>

02:59.054 --> 03:01.973
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:01.973 --> 03:04.684
<i>♪ All your life ♪</i>

03:04.684 --> 03:10.023
<i>♪ All your life,
all your life, all your life ♪</i>

03:10.023 --> 03:14.444
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:14.444 --> 03:17.572
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

03:17.572 --> 03:20.325
<i>♪ You can't believe ♪</i>

03:20.325 --> 03:23.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:23.370 --> 03:28.375
<i>♪ That a match dipped ♪</i>

03:28.375 --> 03:30.960
<i>♪ In gasoline ♪</i>

03:30.960 --> 03:34.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:34.214 --> 03:39.302
<i>♪ Has the power to lift ♪</i>

03:39.302 --> 03:42.806
<i>♪ You from this dream ♪</i>

03:42.806 --> 03:48.311
<i>♪ One I thought to leave ♪</i>

03:48.311 --> 03:53.733
<i>♪ Now I'll go and lead ♪</i>

03:53.733 --> 03:57.445
<i>♪ Anyway time recalls ♪</i>

03:57.445 --> 04:00.156
<i>♪ All your life,
all your life ♪</i>

04:00.156 --> 04:02.992
<i>♪ All your life ♪</i>

04:02.992 --> 04:05.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:05.412 --> 04:08.081
<i>♪ All your life ♪</i>

04:08.081 --> 04:13.586
<i>♪ All your life,
all your life, all your life ♪</i>

04:14.838 --> 04:18.008
<i>I realize our new
predicament isn't ideal.</i>

04:18.008 --> 04:22.387
But where some see problems,
I see opportunities.

04:22.387 --> 04:24.014
Now that the building's gone,

04:24.014 --> 04:27.058
there's no denying we're here
for the long term.

04:27.058 --> 04:28.727
That being the case,

04:28.727 --> 04:30.395
we need a more permanent setup,

04:30.395 --> 04:31.813
starting with
a leadership structure.

04:31.813 --> 04:33.398
You're talking
about an election?

04:33.398 --> 04:36.067
I am.
Someone needs to be in charge.

04:36.067 --> 04:38.987
If we want to survive,
we have to be efficient.

04:38.987 --> 04:40.155
I think it's a great idea.

04:40.155 --> 04:41.281
If we're going
down this road,

04:41.281 --> 04:42.615
I'm throwing my name
in the ring.

04:42.615 --> 04:43.992
Oh, yeah?
Kind of like a dark horse,

04:43.992 --> 04:45.201
JFK kind of vibe?

04:45.201 --> 04:46.995
- I like it.
- If we're gonna do this,

04:46.995 --> 04:48.288
we'll need oversight.

04:48.288 --> 04:49.664
I hereby appoint myself

04:49.664 --> 04:50.957
Election Commissioner.

04:50.957 --> 04:51.958
Please stop.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.460
His nonsense aside,

04:53.460 --> 04:55.462
I'm also putting my name up.

04:55.462 --> 04:57.130
Let's take a few hours
before we reconvene

04:57.130 --> 04:59.507
for speeches and voting.

04:59.507 --> 05:01.301
I'll be watching, so please,

05:01.301 --> 05:02.969
no one even think
about bribing me.

05:02.969 --> 05:04.596
[chuckles] OK.

05:04.596 --> 05:07.640
Wow, local elections.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.225
I guess we're officially
a community, huh?

05:09.225 --> 05:11.978
What do you think
our property tax is gonna be,

05:11.978 --> 05:13.188
three oranges,

05:13.188 --> 05:14.522
a basket of fish?

05:14.522 --> 05:15.565
Well, you're--you're really

05:15.565 --> 05:17.525
taking this in stride.

05:17.525 --> 05:19.694
I don't think
we have a choice.

05:19.694 --> 05:23.281
Lost our way back home,

05:23.281 --> 05:25.325
both my parents.

05:25.325 --> 05:26.993
You know, I just--
I just wanna focus

05:26.993 --> 05:28.703
on you and me
and the kids, right?

05:28.703 --> 05:30.038
Yeah.

05:30.038 --> 05:32.707
[clears throat]
I did get you something.

05:34.918 --> 05:36.127
- What is this?
- Yeah, I--

05:36.127 --> 05:37.087
I got it from the wedding.

05:37.087 --> 05:39.255
Aw, thank you.
It's beautiful.

05:39.255 --> 05:40.507
- Yeah.
- Maybe--

05:40.507 --> 05:43.176
maybe we can go on a--
a long walk,

05:43.176 --> 05:44.302
and I can thank you in private.

05:44.302 --> 05:46.096
Oh, I'd like that.

05:46.096 --> 05:47.305
You're full of good ideas.

05:47.305 --> 05:48.473
- I am full of good ideas.
- Yeah.

05:48.473 --> 05:49.516
- Oh.
- Ow.

05:49.516 --> 05:50.475
- You all right?
- Yeah.

05:50.475 --> 05:51.434
No, it's fine. It's fine.

05:51.434 --> 05:52.977
I'm fine.

05:52.977 --> 05:56.064
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:56.064 --> 06:02.278
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:02.278 --> 06:04.114
[breathes heavily]

06:04.114 --> 06:06.324
Gavin, I'm fine.

06:06.324 --> 06:07.534
- What--what's up?
- I--I know.

06:07.534 --> 06:11.371
I--I've seen this cut before

06:11.371 --> 06:13.373
in my vision.

06:13.373 --> 06:14.582
What are you saying?

06:14.582 --> 06:16.376
It was a fresh wound
on your palm,

06:16.376 --> 06:17.711
same size, same placement.

06:17.711 --> 06:19.963
I'm sure that's just
a coincidence.

06:19.963 --> 06:21.715
Yeah, maybe.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.925
Or maybe it's a sign
my vision's about to happen.

06:23.925 --> 06:27.887
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:33.184 --> 06:36.062
[indistinct chatter]

06:39.149 --> 06:40.984
If you're hungry.

06:44.446 --> 06:45.739
Ty.

06:45.739 --> 06:48.450
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:48.450 --> 06:50.326
I just wanted to say thanks

06:50.326 --> 06:53.621
for getting Paara to let
me stay here while I recover.

06:53.621 --> 06:55.165
Didn't seem like
you had another option.

06:55.165 --> 06:57.792
You're right.

06:57.792 --> 07:00.003
No one at this Clearing wants
to talk to me right now.

07:00.003 --> 07:02.297
I'm sure you can understand
their position.

07:02.297 --> 07:04.466
Yeah, I can.

07:04.466 --> 07:07.552
[sighs] What I can't quite
see is where I go from here.

07:07.552 --> 07:12.557
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:12.557 --> 07:15.769
You know, they say fresh air
is often the best medicine.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.064
Join me for a walk?

07:19.064 --> 07:21.149
What do you say?

07:21.149 --> 07:22.525
[sighs]

07:24.527 --> 07:25.862
<i>Let me ask you a question.</i>

07:25.862 --> 07:27.864
Do you guys see
any of those red trees

07:27.864 --> 07:28.948
around here with the flowers?

07:28.948 --> 07:30.617
- Because I don't.
- Mom, you know

07:30.617 --> 07:31.826
it's not that simple.

07:31.826 --> 07:33.203
Yeah, those trees
are everywhere.

07:33.203 --> 07:34.704
And now we don't even have
a way to get out of here.

07:34.704 --> 07:36.164
But we have been
dealing with this

07:36.164 --> 07:38.166
since we came back down here,
and I'm still standing.

07:38.166 --> 07:39.501
Mom, this is different.

07:39.501 --> 07:41.169
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:41.169 --> 07:43.338
Look, it's just
another challenge, right?

07:43.338 --> 07:46.257
It's just another problem
we have to overcome.

07:46.257 --> 07:47.801
Your mom is right.

07:47.801 --> 07:48.968
We just have
to keep our eyes open

07:48.968 --> 07:51.513
and keep living our lives.

07:51.513 --> 07:54.849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:54.849 --> 07:57.352
OK.
We live our lives.

07:57.352 --> 07:59.062
Yeah.

08:00.271 --> 08:04.192
All right.
I'll go, uh, finish my chores.

08:04.192 --> 08:06.528
I will help.

08:06.528 --> 08:11.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:11.116 --> 08:12.534
It's gonna be OK.

08:12.534 --> 08:14.035
Yeah, I--I know.
I know,

08:14.035 --> 08:16.746
because I'm not gonna lose you.

08:16.746 --> 08:18.331
I'm working on a plan.

08:18.331 --> 08:20.750
We'll figure this out.

08:22.419 --> 08:23.962
[sighs]

08:24.713 --> 08:27.132
[groans]

08:27.132 --> 08:31.302
There's a lot
I've been thinking about,

08:31.302 --> 08:32.804
a lot I need to say.

08:32.804 --> 08:34.806
We don't need to get
into all of that right now.

08:36.599 --> 08:38.768
I'd like to.

08:38.768 --> 08:41.062
To be honest, I could
use someone to talk to.

08:41.062 --> 08:45.150
Levi, I'm not your therapist.

08:45.150 --> 08:51.156
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:51.156 --> 08:52.323
- Are you all right?
- I'm just--

08:52.323 --> 08:54.034
I'm just a little light-headed.
It's OK.

08:55.326 --> 08:58.496
You should really go on
without me.

08:58.496 --> 09:00.081
Here.

09:00.081 --> 09:03.084
[panting]

09:03.084 --> 09:10.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:15.138 --> 09:17.223
You know, I'd like
to go back alone.

09:17.223 --> 09:18.391
No, it's OK.
I'll go with you.

09:18.391 --> 09:20.185
No.

09:20.185 --> 09:22.812
And for the record,
I am far from OK.

09:22.812 --> 09:25.440
I have cancer.

09:25.440 --> 09:27.108
And the pills that would have
helped me were destroyed

09:27.108 --> 09:28.818
when you blew up that building.

09:30.820 --> 09:32.614
Ty, I'm--I'm sorry.

09:32.614 --> 09:34.866
You're sorry?

09:34.866 --> 09:38.119
I had a second chance
at life here.

09:38.119 --> 09:40.288
I was looking forward
to building my life with Paara.

09:40.288 --> 09:41.748
And now whatever time
I have left

09:41.748 --> 09:43.124
has been cut short
because of you.

09:44.751 --> 09:47.462
Like I said,
I'll go back alone.

09:47.462 --> 09:54.678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:59.849 --> 10:02.102
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:03.853 --> 10:05.605
How's the speech coming?

10:05.605 --> 10:08.817
It's no Gettysburg Address,
but it's something.

10:15.949 --> 10:17.826
Hey, what happened
to your wedding ring?

10:17.826 --> 10:20.578
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

10:20.578 --> 10:23.998
Oh, yeah.
I lost it.

10:23.998 --> 10:26.251
Well, you don't seem
too concerned about it.

10:27.877 --> 10:29.212
I don't know where it went.

10:29.212 --> 10:31.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:31.756 --> 10:33.466
I remember when I was eight
and you lost it,

10:33.466 --> 10:35.927
you turned the whole house
upside down for days.

10:37.554 --> 10:39.556
It's just a ring.

10:39.556 --> 10:40.932
That ring means Mom.

10:40.932 --> 10:42.392
It means home.

10:42.392 --> 10:44.185
I know we're stuck for now,

10:44.185 --> 10:46.438
but we can't stop fighting
to get out of here.

10:46.438 --> 10:53.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:57.073 --> 10:58.992
This, for better or worse,
is our home,

10:58.992 --> 11:01.161
and we need--we need
to take pride in that.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.121
And we can do this by,
you know,

11:03.121 --> 11:06.750
picking up after ourselves,
for starters.

11:06.750 --> 11:08.335
Are you practicing
your speech?

11:08.335 --> 11:10.795
Believe me, I need to.

11:10.795 --> 11:13.381
Public speaking is not
my thing.

11:13.381 --> 11:16.092
That might be the cutest
thing I've ever seen you do.

11:16.092 --> 11:17.802
Great.
Well, I hope the rest of them

11:17.802 --> 11:19.512
take me a little bit
more seriously.

11:21.264 --> 11:22.932
This means a lot to you,
doesn't it?

11:24.726 --> 11:26.561
Yeah, I guess.

11:26.561 --> 11:28.646
I mean, I do feel like I could
actually make a difference,

11:28.646 --> 11:30.982
help people.

11:30.982 --> 11:33.193
And I finally--

11:33.193 --> 11:37.280
you know, I think I finally get
what my mom wanted me to be.

11:41.910 --> 11:44.746
Ella always had
a good feeling about you.

11:44.746 --> 11:48.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:48.416 --> 11:50.835
I know you miss her.

11:50.835 --> 11:53.421
Yeah, I do.

11:54.964 --> 11:57.300
But I've been trying
to focus on the future.

11:59.052 --> 12:01.721
If these coordinates
are a piece

12:01.721 --> 12:03.431
of something larger that could
actually get us home,

12:03.431 --> 12:06.226
then I need to--
I need to figure out how.

12:06.226 --> 12:08.978
Well, you figured
the first part out.

12:08.978 --> 12:12.607
If there is more to the story,
you'll find it.

12:12.607 --> 12:14.192
Come here.

12:20.990 --> 12:23.243
Your lips are cold.

12:23.243 --> 12:24.953
Your hands are clammy, as well.

12:24.953 --> 12:27.330
You sure there's
nothing else going on?

12:27.330 --> 12:28.748
No, I'm good.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.208
Yeah?

12:30.208 --> 12:32.961
Maybe you should get Sam
to check you out.

12:32.961 --> 12:35.463
Hey.
I'm ready to hear that speech,

12:35.463 --> 12:36.923
my liege.

12:36.923 --> 12:37.882
Do not call me that.

12:37.882 --> 12:39.300
Oh, my God.

12:39.300 --> 12:41.219
I'm fine.
Go work on your speech.

12:41.219 --> 12:43.513
I'm gonna take another look
at these coordinates.

12:43.513 --> 12:44.889
All right.

12:47.267 --> 12:48.393
Idiot.

12:50.854 --> 12:57.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:57.652 --> 12:59.529
Veronica?

12:59.529 --> 13:01.614
I wanted to talk to you
about something.

13:01.614 --> 13:02.991
Sure.
About what?

13:02.991 --> 13:05.827
Actually, those
coordinates you got there.

13:05.827 --> 13:08.663
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:08.663 --> 13:11.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:14.336 --> 13:17.547
[panting]

13:23.011 --> 13:25.305
Levi.

13:25.305 --> 13:27.432
Kira.

13:27.432 --> 13:28.641
You're alive.

13:28.641 --> 13:30.018
Yes.

13:30.018 --> 13:31.519
I'm not here for a fight.

13:31.519 --> 13:33.146
<i>[tense music]</i>

13:33.146 --> 13:34.314
What do you want?

13:34.314 --> 13:36.358
Help.

13:36.358 --> 13:38.651
Me and the others who survived
the building collapse,

13:38.651 --> 13:40.445
we're trying to start over.

13:40.445 --> 13:43.239
We made shelter
in an old research outpost.

13:43.239 --> 13:44.866
We have food, medicine, water.

13:44.866 --> 13:46.743
But...
[sighs]

13:46.743 --> 13:48.244
We need other things too.

13:48.244 --> 13:50.497
What does that
have to do with me?

13:50.497 --> 13:53.625
Taamet told me
he had a lockbox buried

13:53.625 --> 13:57.045
inside the village,
a 10,000 B.C. survival kit

13:57.045 --> 13:58.380
with tools, weapons, seeds--

13:58.380 --> 14:00.465
everything we need
to live down here.

14:02.300 --> 14:04.552
And you want me
to get it for you?

14:04.552 --> 14:06.554
You can go in there.
I can't.

14:06.554 --> 14:09.099
After everything you've done,
why would I help you?

14:09.099 --> 14:11.059
Because it's not just
about me.

14:11.059 --> 14:12.936
It's everyone you displaced.

14:12.936 --> 14:15.647
Nobody can ever get home again.

14:15.647 --> 14:16.981
Don't you owe them help?

14:16.981 --> 14:22.112
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:22.112 --> 14:24.072
What about a trade?

14:24.072 --> 14:26.741
You say you have medicine.

14:26.741 --> 14:29.244
Do you still have access to
the treatment for Ty's cancer?

14:31.329 --> 14:33.331
I do.

14:33.331 --> 14:35.375
I'm willing to give it to you
if you agree to meet me

14:35.375 --> 14:39.087
with Taamet's box
by the end of the day.

14:39.087 --> 14:41.715
Tell me where to find it.

14:44.009 --> 14:45.593
Silas?

14:45.593 --> 14:47.929
Gavin, my boy.

14:47.929 --> 14:49.264
You're a welcome sight.

14:49.264 --> 14:51.141
I was worried about you.

14:51.141 --> 14:52.559
You look like hell.

14:52.559 --> 14:55.687
Eh, it takes more than
a bullet to strike me down,

14:55.687 --> 14:58.648
not that I have much
to look forward to.

14:58.648 --> 15:01.109
Paara still plans
to hold me accountable

15:01.109 --> 15:04.279
for my past transgressions.

15:04.279 --> 15:05.739
Maybe I can talk to her.

15:05.739 --> 15:08.700
No, I don't think
that would be of any use.

15:08.700 --> 15:10.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:10.452 --> 15:12.954
That's not why you're here,
is it?

15:12.954 --> 15:15.665
No.
No, it's not.

15:15.665 --> 15:17.375
I came to talk to you
about this.

15:18.960 --> 15:21.463
It's Moore's journal.

15:21.463 --> 15:25.300
Now, it turns out
that this is actually a puzzle.

15:25.300 --> 15:28.136
Someone solved it,
and it's coordinates.

15:28.136 --> 15:30.096
They lead to something
down here.

15:30.096 --> 15:31.473
We just don't know what it is.

15:31.473 --> 15:33.183
You don't say.

15:33.183 --> 15:35.143
Now, you worked with Moore.

15:35.143 --> 15:37.687
If anybody can make sense
of it, it's you.

15:39.814 --> 15:42.359
[chuckles]

15:43.777 --> 15:45.403
What is it?

15:45.403 --> 15:48.990
I knew it.
This journal isn't just theory.

15:48.990 --> 15:51.618
This--this is recorded data.

15:51.618 --> 15:54.329
He was working
on real-world experiments.

15:54.329 --> 15:55.497
I don't understand
what that means.

15:55.497 --> 15:57.665
It means Moore needed
a machine

15:57.665 --> 15:59.292
to create this data...

16:01.211 --> 16:03.588
A machine here, in 10,000 B.C.

16:03.588 --> 16:06.508
<i>[exciting music]</i>

16:06.508 --> 16:09.344
You're saying
he made a portal here.

16:09.344 --> 16:11.471
I think there's
a chance, yes.

16:11.471 --> 16:13.765
If he did,

16:13.765 --> 16:16.559
I might finally be able
to get my family home.

16:16.559 --> 16:20.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:25.443 --> 16:26.361
I--I knew Moore better
than anyone.

16:27.404 --> 16:28.530
When he left the building, he--

16:28.530 --> 16:29.989
he lived here in the Village.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.825
He told me he wanted to make
a machine of his own,

16:31.825 --> 16:34.202
a machine that could be
operated safely

16:34.202 --> 16:35.787
and wouldn't create sinkholes.

16:35.787 --> 16:39.457
I didn't know how far
he'd gotten until now.

16:39.457 --> 16:41.376
But I have to warn you.

16:41.376 --> 16:45.922
Moore was incredibly protective
of his work--secretive.

16:45.922 --> 16:49.134
It will not be a simple journey
to find that portal.

16:49.134 --> 16:51.553
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

16:51.553 --> 16:53.388
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:53.388 --> 16:55.265
Time to cast your ballots,

16:55.265 --> 16:57.058
or stones, as it were.

16:57.058 --> 16:59.561
If you're with team Sam,
they go in here.

16:59.561 --> 17:02.230
Team Lucas goes
in the other one.

17:02.230 --> 17:04.149
OK, let's have at it.

17:04.149 --> 17:05.817
Hey, that can wait.

17:05.817 --> 17:07.736
- Everything all right?
- Yeah, more than all right.

17:07.736 --> 17:09.696
I just learned we may still
have a way home.

17:09.696 --> 17:11.781
<i>[tense music]</i>

17:11.781 --> 17:13.241
I thought we lost that
with the building.

17:13.241 --> 17:14.868
I know, so did I.
But I spoke to Silas,

17:14.868 --> 17:17.245
and he believes that
Moore built another portal,

17:17.245 --> 17:19.748
and it's down here,
maybe just 15 miles away.

17:19.748 --> 17:21.916
Ho--hold on.
How do you know where it is?

17:21.916 --> 17:24.502
Veronica figured it out.

17:24.502 --> 17:25.754
She figured out
the coordinates,

17:25.754 --> 17:28.423
and Silas believes
that's what they lead to.

17:28.423 --> 17:31.176
I knew it.
I--I felt it.

17:31.176 --> 17:32.594
We need to check this out now.

17:32.594 --> 17:35.513
But I mean, no one's
ever seen this portal, right?

17:35.513 --> 17:37.349
Just saying, 15 miles, it's a--

17:37.349 --> 17:38.767
it's a long stroll
for a slice of maybe.

17:38.767 --> 17:41.603
I'd walk double that
if it meant we had a chance.

17:41.603 --> 17:42.937
I know this is a lot
to take in,

17:42.937 --> 17:45.273
but if this is a way home,
we can't ignore this.

17:45.273 --> 17:46.691
This could be
how we save you.

17:46.691 --> 17:49.069
<i>[exciting music]</i>

17:49.069 --> 17:51.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:51.154 --> 17:52.739
Yeah.
Everybody who's going,

17:52.739 --> 17:54.199
gather up your stuff.
We'll leave in about an hour.

17:54.199 --> 17:58.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:58.119 --> 17:59.788
Hey, I'll be there
in a second, OK?

17:59.788 --> 18:01.206
OK.

18:03.792 --> 18:05.877
You did this, you know?

18:05.877 --> 18:08.296
You've given us all hope.

18:08.296 --> 18:10.298
I was just following my gut.

18:10.298 --> 18:11.549
Besides, we're not there yet.

18:11.549 --> 18:13.343
Well, if your gut
gets us home,

18:13.343 --> 18:15.220
I'm treating you to a spa day.

18:17.806 --> 18:18.932
[winces]

18:20.850 --> 18:22.811
You don't look so hot.

18:22.811 --> 18:27.649
I've been getting headaches
and dizzy spells and nausea.

18:27.649 --> 18:29.609
Your symptoms could be
from the wasps.

18:29.609 --> 18:32.404
Toxins can stay in the body
for weeks after the sting.

18:32.404 --> 18:35.240
Oh, maybe that's it.

18:35.240 --> 18:37.826
Let me--let me see if I can

18:37.826 --> 18:39.119
find you something
for the pain.

18:39.119 --> 18:40.912
OK.

18:40.912 --> 18:43.873
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

18:43.873 --> 18:50.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:53.216 --> 18:54.801
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

18:56.553 --> 18:58.263
Are you ready to get
the hell out of here?

18:58.263 --> 18:59.556
Yeah.

19:03.226 --> 19:06.062
OK, let's do it.

19:06.062 --> 19:09.065
<i>[exciting music]</i>

19:09.065 --> 19:16.239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:35.133 --> 19:36.760
[groans]

19:41.973 --> 19:42.932
[metallic thunk]

19:53.902 --> 19:55.570
Keeping busy, I see.

19:55.570 --> 19:56.571
This is none
of your business.

19:56.571 --> 19:58.198
- Keep moving.
- What exactly

19:58.198 --> 19:59.240
are you doing here?

19:59.240 --> 20:00.408
I'm not gonna tell you again.

20:00.408 --> 20:02.118
- Go.
- It'd be a shame

20:02.118 --> 20:03.370
if one of the guards were to be

20:03.370 --> 20:05.580
suddenly called over
and saw you here.

20:05.580 --> 20:07.540
I bet you they'd be
very interested

20:07.540 --> 20:09.626
in what you're digging up.

20:11.753 --> 20:12.921
[sighs]

20:14.464 --> 20:16.091
I made a deal with Kira.

20:16.091 --> 20:17.759
<i>[ominous music]</i>

20:17.759 --> 20:19.052
Kira?

20:19.052 --> 20:20.595
She asked me to find this.

20:20.595 --> 20:22.263
And in exchange,
she's gonna give me

20:22.263 --> 20:23.807
cancer medication for Ty.

20:23.807 --> 20:26.851
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:26.851 --> 20:28.269
I'll keep quiet.

20:28.269 --> 20:29.396
But I want in.

20:29.396 --> 20:31.272
What?
No.

20:31.272 --> 20:33.066
- Why?
- I'm to be put

20:33.066 --> 20:34.943
on trial in two days' time.

20:34.943 --> 20:38.113
But if I help save the life
of Paara's husband,

20:38.113 --> 20:39.906
I may earn a reprieve.

20:41.366 --> 20:43.535
[indistinct shouts]

20:43.535 --> 20:45.328
I think they're looking for me.

20:49.249 --> 20:51.626
OK.
You can come with me.

20:51.626 --> 20:53.586
But we need a way out of here.

20:53.586 --> 20:56.297
Getting out of the Village
won't be a problem.

20:56.297 --> 20:58.174
I'll show you the way.

20:58.174 --> 21:05.348
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:12.105 --> 21:14.941
We got a problem.

21:14.941 --> 21:16.818
This direction's too steep
to scale.

21:16.818 --> 21:18.236
We need to find
a way around it.

21:18.236 --> 21:20.655
OK.
Let's scout ahead.

21:20.655 --> 21:22.824
Everyone else, take a break.

21:29.497 --> 21:31.332
Let me go look over here, OK?

21:31.332 --> 21:34.294
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

21:34.294 --> 21:36.421
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:36.421 --> 21:37.964
Hey, idiot.

21:37.964 --> 21:39.215
[chuckles]

21:39.215 --> 21:40.842
Why am I an idiot?

21:40.842 --> 21:43.553
Why haven't you made up
with Riley yet?

21:43.553 --> 21:45.972
I'm not talking about that
with my kid sister.

21:48.558 --> 21:51.644
Look, if things work out,

21:51.644 --> 21:53.521
we make it back home,

21:53.521 --> 21:54.981
real life is gonna
pull everyone

21:54.981 --> 21:56.024
in different directions.

21:56.024 --> 21:58.610
So if you want
a future with Riley,

21:58.610 --> 22:00.862
you need to fix things now.

22:00.862 --> 22:07.535
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:11.039 --> 22:13.416
You know,
you're good at this.

22:13.416 --> 22:15.043
Your dad must be
a great teacher.

22:15.043 --> 22:17.712
He is.

22:17.712 --> 22:20.423
Ooh, you're gonna need
a larger bandage...

22:22.592 --> 22:24.344
Which I don't have.

22:24.344 --> 22:26.012
I'm gonna go see
what my dad's got.

22:36.398 --> 22:43.488
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:53.248 --> 22:55.375
Riley.

22:55.375 --> 22:57.293
Were you and Mom
getting divorced?

22:57.293 --> 23:00.422
All this time, you said
you wanted to get back to her.

23:00.422 --> 23:03.133
Dad, why didn't
you say anything?

23:03.133 --> 23:04.426
Now's not the time.

23:04.426 --> 23:05.760
We might be going home soon.

23:05.760 --> 23:08.596
Now's exactly the time.

23:08.596 --> 23:10.098
You didn't lose your ring.

23:10.098 --> 23:11.766
You took it off.

23:14.436 --> 23:16.271
It's complicated.

23:16.271 --> 23:20.358
Right now we need to focus
on finding that portal.

23:20.358 --> 23:21.693
We found a way around the hill.

23:21.693 --> 23:23.236
- We need to go.
- Dad.

23:23.236 --> 23:26.990
All right, everyone,
let's move out.

23:33.413 --> 23:35.081
We're clear of the Village.

23:35.081 --> 23:37.125
I want to see
what's inside the box.

23:37.125 --> 23:40.587
Kira said it was full
of seeds, tools, and weapons.

23:40.587 --> 23:43.214
It hardly seems big enough
for all that.

23:43.214 --> 23:44.632
I've known Kira for years.

23:44.632 --> 23:48.136
With her,
there's always an angle.

23:48.136 --> 23:50.930
We need to find something
to break this lock with.

23:59.606 --> 24:00.982
[grunts]

24:06.071 --> 24:07.864
Silas?

24:07.864 --> 24:10.492
No, no, no, no, no, no.

24:10.492 --> 24:13.078
Where the hell did you go?

24:13.078 --> 24:16.581
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:16.581 --> 24:22.629
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:26.091 --> 24:29.010
So Gavin thinks we're
about half a kilometer out

24:29.010 --> 24:30.178
from the portal.

24:31.763 --> 24:33.139
[scoffs]
All right.

24:33.139 --> 24:34.683
I know we might be going home
and everything,

24:34.683 --> 24:36.309
but why are you so happy?

24:36.309 --> 24:37.686
This ain't the Judah I know.

24:37.686 --> 24:39.729
Eh, just thinking
about my hot tub,

24:39.729 --> 24:41.648
my hot wife.

24:41.648 --> 24:43.983
Yeah, that's right,
my hot wife.

24:43.983 --> 24:45.443
Didn't know I was married,
did you?

24:45.443 --> 24:48.196
You never asked.

24:48.196 --> 24:49.906
And you're still not
paying attention to me.

24:49.906 --> 24:51.783
No, I'm not, dude,
because I'm looking at that.

24:51.783 --> 24:54.202
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:54.202 --> 24:55.745
Whoa.

24:55.745 --> 24:57.997
Hey, guys.

24:57.997 --> 24:59.749
Over here.

24:59.749 --> 25:06.923
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:08.341 --> 25:09.843
Oh, God.

25:11.886 --> 25:13.304
Did an animal do this?

25:13.304 --> 25:14.931
Yeah, it looks that way.

25:25.025 --> 25:26.818
- Damn it.
- What?

25:26.818 --> 25:28.570
We're here.

25:28.570 --> 25:29.946
This is where
the coordinates end.

25:29.946 --> 25:31.781
Then why are there nothing
but dead bodies here?

25:31.781 --> 25:36.286
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:41.458 --> 25:41.916
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

25:44.461 --> 25:51.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:55.680 --> 25:59.225
Eve.
They had a kid with them.

25:59.225 --> 26:00.852
Who were these people?

26:00.852 --> 26:03.271
I'm more concerned
with what did this to them.

26:03.271 --> 26:10.278
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:13.198 --> 26:14.699
No way.

26:17.535 --> 26:19.829
You all right, man?

26:19.829 --> 26:22.082
Uh, the day
we fell down here,

26:22.082 --> 26:25.251
I was actually on my way
to a job interview.

26:25.251 --> 26:27.754
We were set to meet
at a café near the Peterson.

26:27.754 --> 26:29.297
Yeah?

26:32.133 --> 26:35.136
This is their business card.

26:35.136 --> 26:37.889
That's the same symbol
as this locket.

26:37.889 --> 26:39.808
What does that mean?

26:39.808 --> 26:41.393
I have no freaking idea.

26:41.393 --> 26:43.353
Hey, guys, check it out.

26:43.353 --> 26:45.271
We've got something.

26:48.817 --> 26:51.319
I think it's a lockbox.

26:53.947 --> 26:55.699
Do you have that key,

26:55.699 --> 26:57.784
the one you found
with Moore's skeleton?

26:57.784 --> 26:59.411
Yeah.

27:12.215 --> 27:19.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:21.391 --> 27:24.185
Looks like a map
to some kind of cave system.

27:24.185 --> 27:25.770
That could be
where the portal is.

27:25.770 --> 27:27.814
Then that's
where we're going.

27:27.814 --> 27:30.650
<i>[epic music]</i>

27:30.650 --> 27:37.824
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:39.284 --> 27:41.411
Silas! Hey.

27:41.411 --> 27:43.038
[grunts, coughs]

27:43.038 --> 27:45.165
Stay away, or I'll break
your ribs again.

27:45.165 --> 27:47.375
That box is my only way
to help Ty.

27:47.375 --> 27:48.835
I have to get it to Kira.

27:48.835 --> 27:50.879
You're a fool if you think
she'll help you.

27:50.879 --> 27:53.214
Kira took my daughter
away from me.

27:53.214 --> 27:55.383
I'm gonna use this box
to get close to her.

27:55.383 --> 27:57.385
Then I'll make her pay
for what she's done.

27:57.385 --> 27:58.678
Listen to me.

27:58.678 --> 28:00.472
Killing Kira will not
bring your daughter back.

28:00.472 --> 28:02.474
And it sure as hell will not
make you feel any better.

28:02.474 --> 28:03.975
You have no idea
what you're talking about!

28:03.975 --> 28:05.894
Actually, I do.

28:05.894 --> 28:08.396
I lost my daughter.

28:08.396 --> 28:10.440
And when she died,
it was like someone put

28:10.440 --> 28:13.318
a thousand-pound weight
on my chest.

28:13.318 --> 28:15.487
And I thought that if I could
stop the thing that hurt her,

28:15.487 --> 28:17.655
if I destroyed Lazarus,
then maybe that weight

28:17.655 --> 28:18.740
would finally go away.

28:18.740 --> 28:21.534
But it's still right here.

28:21.534 --> 28:24.287
Revenge doesn't fix the pain.

28:31.294 --> 28:34.923
Maybe we can get justice
and those pills.

28:38.134 --> 28:39.594
What do you have in mind?

28:39.594 --> 28:46.434
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:48.395 --> 28:50.897
No improvement
since this morning?

28:50.897 --> 28:53.858
No.
But like you said,

28:53.858 --> 28:56.111
it's probably just
from the wasp sting.

28:58.780 --> 29:02.492
You know, whatever
you tell me stays between us.

29:06.621 --> 29:10.500
You know what I took from
your medical kit, don't you?

29:10.500 --> 29:11.835
The pregnancy test.

29:11.835 --> 29:14.295
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

29:14.295 --> 29:17.007
Did you take it?

29:17.007 --> 29:19.175
No, not yet.

29:19.175 --> 29:20.969
It's okay to be nervous.

29:20.969 --> 29:23.972
I don't know how to be a mom.

29:23.972 --> 29:25.640
I didn't exactly have
great role models

29:25.640 --> 29:26.975
in the parent department.

29:26.975 --> 29:28.435
So you know what not to do.

29:28.435 --> 29:30.061
But the first thing
about being a mom

29:30.061 --> 29:31.187
is knowing if you are one.

29:32.689 --> 29:34.149
Yeah, you're right.

29:36.401 --> 29:38.361
I'll tell Lucas
what's going on.

29:40.196 --> 29:42.365
And then I'll take the test.

29:42.365 --> 29:43.783
[branch snaps]

29:43.783 --> 29:47.078
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:47.078 --> 29:52.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:52.542 --> 29:53.960
Wait!

30:15.440 --> 30:17.025
Hey.

30:17.025 --> 30:20.111
Hey, it's okay.
I'm a friend.

30:23.740 --> 30:25.075
Is this yours?

30:25.075 --> 30:32.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:32.248 --> 30:34.292
Here.

30:38.630 --> 30:40.382
It's okay.

30:45.637 --> 30:47.305
What is it, Iz?

30:47.305 --> 30:49.265
It's one of those flowers.

30:53.728 --> 30:55.563
Iz, where are you going?

30:55.563 --> 31:02.570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:12.372 --> 31:14.874
To get to Moore's portal,
we have to go through there.

31:14.874 --> 31:18.628
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:23.842 --> 31:24.718
I'm really sorry
to hear this.

31:25.760 --> 31:28.304
Can't imagine how hard this is.

31:28.304 --> 31:31.433
But if Eve is in danger,
others could be too.

31:31.433 --> 31:33.685
Why don't a few of us go ahead
to the cave,

31:33.685 --> 31:36.396
then circle back once we know
everything's safe?

31:36.396 --> 31:37.772
I think that's a smart plan.

31:37.772 --> 31:39.274
I'll go with you.

31:39.274 --> 31:41.026
Someone needs to look
after the people here.

31:41.026 --> 31:42.569
I'll stay.

31:42.569 --> 31:45.822
<i>[tense music]</i>

31:45.822 --> 31:52.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:52.120 --> 31:55.498
Eve, what do you think?

31:57.834 --> 31:59.252
I think I should stay.

31:59.252 --> 32:01.838
- All right.
- Come here.

32:01.838 --> 32:03.965
We're gonna get through this.

32:03.965 --> 32:07.010
I'll be back
before you know it.

32:07.010 --> 32:09.471
- Love you, Mom.
- Love you.

32:09.471 --> 32:11.139
You got this.

32:14.517 --> 32:16.269
[sighs]

32:16.269 --> 32:19.481
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:19.481 --> 32:26.446
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:32.535 --> 32:34.537
You didn't say
you were bringing friends.

32:34.537 --> 32:36.122
All kinds
of dangers out here.

32:36.122 --> 32:39.334
Better to be safe.

32:39.334 --> 32:41.836
Let's just do the trade.
I brought my part.

32:41.836 --> 32:44.005
So did I.

32:44.005 --> 32:46.549
But I do need to check
one thing first.

32:49.219 --> 32:50.720
What's with
the Geiger counter?

32:53.807 --> 32:55.308
Those are fuel rods.

32:55.308 --> 32:57.852
You need them for any machine
that manipulates time.

32:57.852 --> 32:59.479
But I destroyed your machine.

32:59.479 --> 33:02.065
You destroyed the first one.

33:02.065 --> 33:03.483
After reading Moore's journal,

33:03.483 --> 33:06.319
I think he might have
built another.

33:06.319 --> 33:08.571
This isn't Taamet's box.

33:08.571 --> 33:11.199
This was Moore's.
You lied to me.

33:11.199 --> 33:12.409
I'm still gonna need it.

33:12.409 --> 33:14.202
Wait, if there's another
way to get us home,

33:14.202 --> 33:16.162
- we can all use it.
- We tried that last time.

33:16.162 --> 33:17.372
Well, then I'm not
giving you the box.

33:17.372 --> 33:18.707
You don't have a choice.

33:18.707 --> 33:23.753
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:23.753 --> 33:24.796
Ah!

33:24.796 --> 33:27.757
[groaning]

33:31.720 --> 33:34.055
Good work, Silas.

33:34.055 --> 33:35.932
Take her to the Village.

33:35.932 --> 33:43.106
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:48.570 --> 33:49.904
[sighs]

33:49.904 --> 33:57.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:05.628 --> 34:07.630
Your daughter's death
changed you.

34:11.009 --> 34:13.887
You helped people today,

34:13.887 --> 34:15.805
including my husband.

34:19.726 --> 34:22.228
Perhaps you deserve
another chance.

34:24.147 --> 34:26.316
Don't waste this.

34:26.316 --> 34:33.448
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:34.824 --> 34:37.786
I was hoping I could ask you
a couple of questions,

34:37.786 --> 34:40.914
like how long
have you been here?

34:40.914 --> 34:43.166
Where are you from?

34:48.338 --> 34:51.257
Hey.
Hi.

34:51.257 --> 34:53.468
I'm sure you're
probably pretty scared

34:53.468 --> 34:55.387
being down here alone, huh?

34:55.387 --> 34:56.846
My name is Eve.

34:56.846 --> 35:00.308
What's your name?

35:00.308 --> 35:03.144
Petra.
<i>Ich heisse Petra.</i>

35:03.144 --> 35:05.814
Well, that explains
why she doesn't understand us.

35:05.814 --> 35:07.440
Anybody speak German?

35:07.440 --> 35:10.026
Yeah, actually.
I studied it for two semesters.

35:10.026 --> 35:11.486
Let's see what I can remember.

35:11.486 --> 35:12.987
<i>Guten tag, Petra.</i>

35:12.987 --> 35:16.366
<i>Ich spreche nur
ein bisschen Deutsch.</i>

35:16.366 --> 35:18.743
[speaking German]

35:18.743 --> 35:20.245
That's great.
Keep going.

35:20.245 --> 35:23.331
<i>Uh, mein name ist Scott.</i>

35:23.331 --> 35:25.166
Hey.
How you feeling?

35:25.166 --> 35:26.793
Better, I think.

35:28.461 --> 35:30.005
I want to talk to you
about something.

35:30.005 --> 35:31.965
Yeah.

35:31.965 --> 35:35.301
You know, there's something
I want to say to you too.

35:35.301 --> 35:38.346
Truth is, the closer
we get to going home,

35:38.346 --> 35:41.266
the more I'm not sure
it's what I want.

35:41.266 --> 35:43.059
You want to stay here,

35:43.059 --> 35:46.229
with saber tooths
and no plumbing?

35:46.229 --> 35:48.982
I'm a better person here.

35:48.982 --> 35:51.651
I mean, I could be
the freaking mayor, right?

35:51.651 --> 35:53.862
I can't be that same guy
up there.

35:53.862 --> 35:55.405
Well, what if we work
on it together?

35:55.405 --> 35:56.823
Sure, okay.

35:56.823 --> 35:59.200
Or I ruin everything close
to me like I did before.

35:59.200 --> 36:02.162
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

36:02.162 --> 36:04.205
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:04.205 --> 36:05.623
[sighs]
What?

36:05.623 --> 36:07.459
What are you thinking now?

36:09.878 --> 36:12.380
I need to tell you something,
but I don't--

36:12.380 --> 36:13.840
maybe now's not a good time.

36:13.840 --> 36:16.801
[thunder crashes]

36:18.636 --> 36:19.888
Hey.

36:19.888 --> 36:21.222
We need to find shelter.

36:21.222 --> 36:22.390
There's more caves
around here.

36:22.390 --> 36:23.391
We should find one.

36:23.391 --> 36:25.143
Petra, we need to, uh,

36:25.143 --> 36:26.519
<i>gehen</i> to a cave--

36:26.519 --> 36:29.814
to a--a <i>hohle.</i>

36:31.399 --> 36:34.194
<i>Nein.
Nein.</i>

36:34.194 --> 36:37.072
Uh, monster.

36:37.072 --> 36:40.784
Monster.
Monster.

36:40.784 --> 36:42.952
Monster?

36:42.952 --> 36:44.454
Petra, what do you mean?

36:52.462 --> 36:54.547
Ask her where she saw that.

36:54.547 --> 36:56.800
Uh, <i>wo ist das?</i>

37:02.347 --> 37:04.265
That's the direction
everyone went.

37:04.265 --> 37:06.267
I have to warn them.

37:06.267 --> 37:07.602
What about Gavin's vision?

37:07.602 --> 37:09.104
I'm not letting
my family walk into danger.

37:09.104 --> 37:10.855
I'm going.

37:10.855 --> 37:13.483
- Okay, then I am too.
- Okay, fine. Let's move.

37:18.530 --> 37:18.988
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:21.282 --> 37:25.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:25.412 --> 37:26.746
Based on the map,

37:26.746 --> 37:28.790
the portal must be
somewhere nearby.

37:30.375 --> 37:32.585
What is this?

37:32.585 --> 37:35.505
Looks like it's been
retrofitted for some reason.

37:42.137 --> 37:43.680
Jesus.

37:46.850 --> 37:50.061
This looks like
an animal made it.

37:50.061 --> 37:54.649
Yeah, a really
frickin' big one.

37:56.526 --> 37:59.070
Let's just keep going, okay?

37:59.070 --> 38:03.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:05.535 --> 38:08.496
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

38:08.496 --> 38:10.457
[footsteps approach]

38:10.457 --> 38:13.835
It's good to see
that smile again.

38:13.835 --> 38:16.588
Honestly, I was starting
to give up hope.

38:16.588 --> 38:18.340
I don't know
if these are gonna cure me,

38:18.340 --> 38:21.509
but it's more
than I had before.

38:21.509 --> 38:24.554
And now we have
a future together.

38:24.554 --> 38:26.514
And that future begins today.

38:28.183 --> 38:29.684
Paara.

38:31.144 --> 38:33.521
I'll be right back.

38:37.359 --> 38:43.531
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:43.531 --> 38:46.284
I, uh,
wanted to say thank you

38:46.284 --> 38:47.952
for what you did for me today.

38:49.704 --> 38:52.499
I also wanted to apologize.

38:52.499 --> 38:54.000
I shouldn't have snapped
at you earlier.

38:54.000 --> 38:57.379
No, it's understandable.

38:57.379 --> 39:00.006
I just hope
that I've made it up to you.

39:00.006 --> 39:02.926
No better amends than
potentially saving my life.

39:05.095 --> 39:09.349
So...

39:09.349 --> 39:12.727
where do you go from here?

39:12.727 --> 39:16.898
I took away the chance
for a lot of people to go home.

39:16.898 --> 39:20.110
Maybe if I bring this box
to them, it'll help.

39:20.110 --> 39:23.947
Well, I'd like to help too.
Want some company?

39:23.947 --> 39:26.324
Feels like I owe you a walk
from this morning.

39:29.494 --> 39:32.122
I'd like that.

39:32.122 --> 39:35.125
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:35.125 --> 39:40.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:42.549 --> 39:44.968
There's something
through here.

39:48.972 --> 39:50.765
This is it.

39:55.478 --> 39:56.980
Is the portal in there?

39:56.980 --> 39:58.773
[rocks shifting]

39:58.773 --> 39:59.691
You hear that?

39:59.691 --> 40:01.943
[footsteps approaching]

40:01.943 --> 40:04.487
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:04.487 --> 40:06.781
- Are you guys okay?
- Mom?

40:06.781 --> 40:07.824
Hey.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

40:07.824 --> 40:09.409
Hey.
What are you doing?

40:09.409 --> 40:10.493
I thought you were
gonna stay put.

40:10.493 --> 40:11.786
I had to warn you.

40:11.786 --> 40:15.081
There's something here,
something dangerous.

40:15.081 --> 40:17.417
What?
Gavin?

40:18.835 --> 40:19.919
Look.

40:19.919 --> 40:26.509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:33.641 --> 40:35.727
This is what I saw.

40:37.062 --> 40:40.565
[creature growling]

40:40.565 --> 40:42.150
It's coming towards us.

40:42.150 --> 40:45.195
[thudding]

40:45.195 --> 40:48.156
[lizard hissing]

40:51.576 --> 40:54.746
[lizard screeches]

40:57.248 --> 40:58.917
[whimpers]

40:58.917 --> 41:00.085
Dad!

41:03.713 --> 41:05.465
[grunts]
[lizard roars]

41:05.465 --> 41:08.635
[panting]

41:08.635 --> 41:10.845
[lizard screeches]

41:16.142 --> 41:17.811
- You okay?
- Yeah.

41:19.270 --> 41:20.563
- I'm okay.
- Dad!

41:20.563 --> 41:23.525
[gasping]

41:23.525 --> 41:25.485
[echoing] No.
Gavin!

41:25.485 --> 41:28.697
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:28.697 --> 41:31.241
No.
Gavin.

41:31.241 --> 41:32.909
Gavin!

41:32.909 --> 41:39.582
<i>♪ ♪</i>
